<br>
Learn which dorfs to pull at the Den camp.<br>
By killing just Den and the two dorfs that spawn in the northern hut in the camp and avoiding the fisherman, you only lose Kaladim Citizen faction (which is only applied to mobs in Butcherblock, not in Kaladim...and they're not important for anything as far as I know)<br>
Killing the merchant in the south hut gives bad beta-neutral faction, no loot, no xp<br>
Killing the fisherman gives positive ogre warrior faction, but bad Kaladim city factions.<br>
<br>
Loot: each dorf spawns with an axe worth 3-5pp from the druid vendor just around the corner. They also drop several other FS weapons, 6g-5pp in cash, and assorted ringmail loot. A &quot;quad&quot; of those three dorfs will likely net you about 10-30pp each time. Get rich quick. Enjoy. Make some extra off of TLs to wandering people when druids are too lazy to do it themselves.<br>
<br>
--Allabarnet<br>
--Cazic-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utheflyingwombat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Flying Wombat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/21/02 4:29:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=274.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need Advise Quading Specs in OOT</span><hr size=1> At 45 you can quadkite the specs in OOT for insane exp as long as you can get it done right.  I'd have to say that a large supply of sow potions or jboots is a must (or travelers boots) you will also need a staff of temp flux. Also make sure you have plenty of batwings.  <br>
<br>
First levitate yourself and sow yourself. Next pull spectres with temp flux staff. Then run them around the island til there close together.  Next use your best AE non rain/pb spell. Rinse repeat.  You may have to resnare once or twice and if you get resisted by some on the initial snare just run around the island til all snares wear off and run them back into a group and then snare them again.   Keep a gate up to gfay or somewhere in case things get hairy. I had myself bound in an out of the way place on the island in case I died. <br>
<br>
I quadkited spectres from level 45 to 47 and got through those two levels in less than a 4 days. Not sure what my exact playing time was but I didn't play  a lot for each of the days <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchifiir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/02 11:11:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=274.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Specs in OOT</span><hr size=1> There's another island within view of the Spec island, to the East I think.  Nothing on it but a bunch of very green island goblins and the Oracle of Ak'anon with his guard.<br>
<br>
Run to Spec island, flux specs and run to the water, avoiding the gargoyles.  Round the specs up in the water and kite them on the other island (island goblins/Oracle island.)  If you just kite them around the perimiter, they'll all be dead by about the first full circle.<br>
That island is much flatter, and considerably easier to kite on.  When you're done, just sit at the water's edge facing the spec island.  Goblins don't wander that far down there.<br>
<br>
Kind of annoying to sell of the Scythes, so Oasis is better in that regard, but if you're just hunting xp and don't care about the cash it's not a problem.  I'm KOS to all the vendors I can find, so I just ditch the cash.<br>
<br>
